################################################################################
# Alert Manager Configuration Reference
################################################################################
#
# Route Configuration:
# - receiver: Default receiver name (required)
# - group_by: List of labels to group alerts by
# - group_wait: Time to wait before sending initial notification (default: 30s)
# - group_interval: Time to wait before sending updated notification (default: 5m)
# - repeat_interval: Time to wait before re-sending notification (default: 4h, max: 5 days)
# - continue: Whether to continue matching subsequent routes (default: false)
# - match: Equality matchers (key-value pairs)
# - match_re: Regex matchers (key-regex pairs)
# - routes: Child routes for conditional routing
#
# Receiver Configuration (SNS):
# - name: Receiver name (required)
# - sns_configs: List of SNS configurations
#   - topic_arn: ARN of the SNS topic (required)
#   - sigv4: SigV4 authentication (required)
#     - region: AWS region (required)
#   - subject: Custom subject template (optional)
#   - message: Custom message template (optional)
#   - attributes: Custom SNS message attributes (optional)
#     - key: Attribute name
#     - value: Attribute value
#
# Inhibition Rules:
# - source_match: Labels that must match in source alerts
# - source_match_re: Regex labels that must match in source alerts
# - target_match: Labels that must match in target alerts
# - target_match_re: Regex labels that must match in target alerts
# - equal: Labels that must have equal values in source and target
#
# Template Files:
# - Use Prometheus template language (Go templates)
# - Define custom subjects and messages
# - Access alert data via template variables
# - Reference: https://prometheus.io/docs/prometheus/latest/configuration/template_reference/

################################################################################
# Important Notes and Best Practices
################################################################################
#
# 1. Configuration Format:
#    - Must use YAML format with alertmanager_config root key
#    - Template files are optional but powerful for customization
#    - Indentation is critical in YAML - use consistent spacing
#
# 2. Receiver Limitations:
#    - Only Amazon SNS is currently supported
#    - Other receiver types (email, webhook, etc.) will cause rejection
#    - SNS topic must be in the same region as the workspace
#
# 3. Repeat Interval Constraint:
#    - Maximum repeat_interval is 5 days
#    - Values exceeding 5 days are automatically capped
#    - Consider alert fatigue when setting intervals
#
# 4. IAM Permissions:
#    - Alert Manager needs permission to publish to SNS topics
#    - Use SNS topic policy to grant aps.amazonaws.com access
#    - Include SourceAccount condition for security
#
# 5. Region Consistency:
#    - SNS sigv4 region must match SNS topic ARN region
#    - Cross-region SNS publishing is not supported
#    - Ensure workspace and SNS topics are in the same region
#
# 6. Grouping Strategy:
#    - Group related alerts to reduce notification noise
#    - Common grouping: ['alertname', 'cluster', 'service']
#    - Balance between context and notification volume
#
# 7. Routing Best Practices:
#    - Define specific routes before catch-all routes
#    - Use severity labels for prioritization
#    - Consider team-based routing for organizational efficiency
#    - Test routing rules thoroughly before production
#
# 8. Inhibition Rules:
#    - Use to suppress redundant alerts
#    - Example: Suppress service alerts when node is down
#    - Define clear source and target relationships
#    - Test inhibition logic in non-production first
#
# 9. Template Customization:
#    - Use templates to format messages for clarity
#    - Include relevant context (severity, description, etc.)
#    - Test templates with sample alert data
#    - Reference Prometheus template documentation
#
# 10. Monitoring and Troubleshooting:
#     - Enable CloudWatch Logs for Alert Manager
#     - Monitor CloudWatch metrics:
#       - SecretFetchFailure
#       - AlertManagerNotificationsThrottledByIntegration
#       - AlertManagerNotificationsFailedByIntegration
#     - Check SNS topic delivery status
#     - Verify SNS topic policies and subscriptions
#
# 11. Configuration Updates:
#     - Changes apply immediately without downtime
#     - Validate YAML syntax before applying
#     - Test in development environment first
#     - Keep backup of working configurations
#
# 12. SNS Topic Design:
#     - Separate topics for different severity levels
#     - Team-specific topics for better ownership
#     - Configure appropriate SNS subscriptions (email, Lambda, etc.)
#     - Set up dead-letter queues for failed deliveries
#
# 13. Silence Management:
#     - Silences are configured via Prometheus API, not Terraform
#     - Use for planned maintenance windows
#     - Document silence procedures in runbooks
#
# 14. Testing Strategy:
#     - Create test alerts to verify routing
#     - Validate SNS topic delivery
#     - Test inhibition rules behavior
#     - Verify template rendering
#
# 15. Cost Considerations:
#     - SNS publishes incur charges per message
#     - Group alerts to reduce SNS API calls
#     - Set appropriate repeat intervals
#     - Monitor SNS usage in Cost Explorer

